# Build Versioning

The game shows a build badge in the bottom-right of the screen (e.g. `Dev V0.2.0a`).
The single source of truth is `GAME_VERSION` in `apps/client/src/version.ts`.

## Rule: bump the PATCH number on every change

For now we are in early iteration: after making a meaningful code/content change,
increment ONLY the PATCH (last) number of `GAME_VERSION`.
Format: `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH` (e.g. `0.1.4` → `0.1.5` → `0.1.6`).

| Change type | What to bump | Example |
|-------------|--------------|---------|
| Any change (fix, tweak, feature, polish) | PATCH (last number) | `0.1.4` → `0.1.5` |

Do NOT bump MAJOR or MINOR. The repo owner decides when to shift to `0.2`, `0.3`,
`1.0`, etc. — never do this on your own.

## How

Edit only the one line in `apps/client/src/version.ts`:

```typescript
export const GAME_VERSION = '0.1.5';
```

Do not hardcode the version anywhere else — import `GAME_VERSION` / `VERSION_LABEL`
from `version.ts` instead.
